{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Project Organizer & Documentation Curator",
  "description": "Monitors all markdown documentation and JavaScript test files to categorize, organize, and maintain project knowledge. Reads documentation titles and first lines to create a structured catalog. Identifies deprecated documentation for cleanup and generates mini reports/READMEs for manual review.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileCreated",
    "patterns": [
      "*.md",
      "test-*.js",
      "*-test.js",
      "scripts/*.js",
      "**/*.md"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "You are the Project Organizer Agent. Your responsibilities:\n\n1. **Categorize Documentation**: Read all markdown files (*.md) and extract:\n   - Document title (first heading or filename)\n   - First 1-2 lines of content\n   - Category (feature docs, fix summaries, guides, implementation notes, etc.)\n   - Related files or dependencies mentioned\n\n2. **Categorize Tests**: Read all test files (test-*.js) and extract:\n   - Test purpose from filename and first comments\n   - What features/components they test\n   - Group by domain (auth, medications, devices, caregiver, patient, etc.)\n\n3. **Identify Deprecated Content**: Flag documentation that appears:\n   - Outdated (references old implementations)\n   - Superseded by newer docs\n   - Incomplete or abandoned\n   - Duplicate information\n\n4. **Generate Organization Report**: Create a structured catalog with:\n   - Documentation organized by category and feature area\n   - Test files mapped to their corresponding features\n   - List of deprecated files recommended for cleanup\n   - Mini README summarizing the project's documentation structure\n\n5. **Output Format**: Generate a comprehensive markdown report that includes:\n   - Table of contents by category\n   - Quick reference guide to find relevant docs\n   - Cleanup recommendations with reasoning\n   - Suggestions for missing documentation\n\nFocus on non-exclusive working code (documentation and tests), NOT application source code in src/ or app/ directories.\n\nAnalyze the changed files and update your organizational catalog accordingly."
  }
}